title: The State Fair Affair: Machinery vs Ninjas
Nature Valley Bike Fest Fun Rides
description: Nature Valley Grand Prix kids\' fun races & Recreational Rides
course: Portions of the professional race courses, including the start lines for the kids\' fun races.  Rural roads around Menomonie, Wisconsin, for the recreational rides
registration: On-line and on-site registration.  Kids\' races are free and open to kids ages 12 and under.  Recreational rides are open to everyone.
notes:
For the kids\' fun races, all children must have a wheeled vehicle (in good working order), a helmet and a parent to sign the waiver.

For the recreational rides, everyone must have a bicycle  (in good working order), a helmet and sign the waiver.
directions:
Saint Paul - Exit I-94 @ Eastbound Kellogg.  Left on Saint Peter.

Cannon Falls - Hwy 52 South, East on Hwy 19

Minneapolis - 35th Ave West from I-35W, right on Hennepin.

Menomonie - I-94 West, South from Broadway Ave exit

Stillwater - Hwy 36 East from I-694. 

See web site for more information.

title: Jolly Roger Race #3
registration:
Registration available on site starting at 9am.

A $5 one day USA Cycling license will be required for any racers that are not annual USA cyling members.
directions:
Take Interstate 35 north to Cloquet (approx. 2 hours). 

Take the Range Cities exit (Hwy. 33), stay on Hwy. 33 until it merges with Hwy. 53N. 

Follow Hwy. 53N (approx. 20 miles).  Follow Hwy. 53N until you reach Eveleth (approx. 42 miles). 

When you get to Eveleth, take the Hwy. 37E exit INTO Gilbert, follow that down Main Street. 

You will come to the intersection of Hwy. 135E.  (Right exit)  Follow that for approx. 9 miles to Biwabik.  You will be on Main Street. 

The Giants Ridge exit is approx. 1-1/2 miles FROM the City of Biwabik on the left side of the road.  You will make a left turn onto County Road 138. 

Follow County Road 138 for 3-1/2 miles and Giants Ridge Golf & Ski Resort will be on your left.
